<HEAD>Clinic's New Home Burns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An arson fire caused $ 5,000 damage to an abortion clinic that had moved in the hope of escaping further attention of abortion protesters, authorities said. Flammable liquid was thrown against the <ORGANIZATION> Allegheny </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reproductive </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> entrance early Wednesday, then was ignited, said Deputy Fire Chief <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Harper </PERSON>. The fire damaged the door, a staircase and an awning, <PERSON> Harper </PERSON> said. No arrests were made. The building was unoccupied when the fire broke out, said executive director <PERSON> Claire </PERSON> <PERSON> Keyes </PERSON>. `` We're very thankful that there were no injuries when this terroristic act occurred,'' she said. `` We want to assure our patients that services will be continuing uninterrupted.'' During the weekend, the clinic moved from a building across the street, where several protests had been staged.
