U2 and veteran bluesman B.B King earned a best video from film trophy for `` When Love Comes to Town'' from the concert movie `` Rattle and Hum.'' The awards show, hosted by <ORGANIZATION> Arsenio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hall </ORGANIZATION>, lasted 2 -LCB- hours and featured performances by <PERSON> Abdul </PERSON>, <PERSON> Cher </PERSON>, <PERSON> Def </PERSON> <PERSON> Leppard </PERSON>, <PERSON> Jon </PERSON> <PERSON> Bon </PERSON> <PERSON> Jovi </PERSON>, <PERSON> Richie </PERSON> <PERSON> Sambora </PERSON>, and <PERSON> Madonna </PERSON>. A performance by <ORGANIZATION> MTV </ORGANIZATION> comic <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> <PERSON> Dice </PERSON> <PERSON> Clay </PERSON> was filled with obscene, unprintable poems and comments about overweight women and sex. MTV Vice President <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> Kluger </PERSON> quickly went before reporters backstage and apologized for the material. `` <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> <PERSON> Dice </PERSON> <PERSON> Clay </PERSON> did not do this in rehearsal and we were very surprised by it. Based on this experience, <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> <PERSON> Dice </PERSON> <PERSON> Clay </PERSON> will not be appearing on <ORGANIZATION> MTV </ORGANIZATION> in the future,'' <PERSON> Kluger </PERSON> said. The comic had already left before <PERSON> Kluger </PERSON>'s statement. Pop superstar <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> had the odds in his favor going into the show, but he cashed in only one of his eight nominations, earning a special effects trophy for <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Blashfield </PERSON>. <PERSON> Jody </PERSON> <PERSON> Watley </PERSON> came up emptyhanded despite six nominations for `` Real Love.'' Puerto Rican singer <PERSON> Chayanne </PERSON> won best Latin rock video in the International Viewers Choice award, a popularity contest determined by telephone votes and ballots received by mail and fax machine. Nominations were made in 18 general and professional categories. The additional special categories included Hall of Fame, <ORGANIZATION> Viewers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Choice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Viewers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Choice </ORGANIZATION>, the latter for best European, Australian, Japanese and Latin rock videos. <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> was a multiple winner at the first MTV Video Music Awards in 1984, taking the special Viewer's Choice, choreography and overall performance honors for `` Thriller.'' But even then he was overshadowed by <PERSON> Herbie </PERSON> <PERSON> Hancock </PERSON>'s six awards for `` Rockit.'' <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> did n't get another <ORGANIZATION> MTV </ORGANIZATION> award until last year, when he was given a special Video Vanguard award. And despite an emphasis on stunning visuals, <PERSON> Madonna </PERSON> did n't win an <ORGANIZATION> MTV </ORGANIZATION> award until 1986. Her second came in 1987. In the short history of the <ORGANIZATION> MTV </ORGANIZATION> awards, <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Gabriel </PERSON> was the biggest winner of a single year, collecting nine silver statuettes for `` Sledgehammer'' in 1987. The first and second MTV awards were staged at Radio City Music Hall in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. The 1986 show originated from both the Universal Amphitheatre and the Palladium in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. Since then the amphitheater has been its home.
