of the stock market to unstable exchange rates and the weakness of the yen. `` Many investors are sidelined until the instability of exchange rates settles down,'' said a dealer at <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION>, speaking on condition of anonymity. He added that buying incentives are increasing in the market though `` the Nikkei average is not improving yet,'' he said. The volume traded on the first section of the exchange, where most major shares are listed, was estimated at a moderate 600 million shares.
