<HEAD>Informant, Three Others Arrested in Shooting of Agents</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By COLLEEN BARRY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>FRESNO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The informant who helped arrange a <ORGANIZATION> Border </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patrol </ORGANIZATION> sting aimed at smuggling of illegal aliens was arrested on suspicion of murder after the bust went awry. One federal agent was slain and his partner wounded. Four people in all were arrested in the shooting in a convenience store parking lot early Wednesday. Agent <PERSON> Keith </PERSON> <PERSON> Connelly </PERSON>, 42, an 18-year Border Patrol veteran, died of a gunshot wound to the chest. His partner, <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Jordan </PERSON>, also shot in the chest, was downgraded from serious to critical condition today. <PERSON> Connelly </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jordan </PERSON> had arranged through the informant, an illegal alien farmhand, to meet a group of smugglers at the store, said <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Carter </PERSON>, chief <ORGANIZATION> Border </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patrol </ORGANIZATION> agent. He said the agents posed as employers offering to pay about $ 500 for the alien and were about to make arrests when they were shot. The agents had met the informant Saturday, and he did not tell them the smugglers would be armed, <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> said. After the shooting, the informant fled. Authorities could not immediately say what his role was in the shootings. `` At this time I have no idea whether or not it was a setup,'' <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> said. Arrested on suspicion of murder and other, unspecified, charges were <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> <PERSON> Macias </PERSON> <PERSON> Arreola </PERSON>, 41, <PERSON> Florentino </PERSON> <PERSON> Nunez </PERSON> <PERSON> Mujica </PERSON>, 31, and <PERSON> Rosura </PERSON> <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON>, 22, all of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, and <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Serrano </PERSON> <PERSON> Saldana </PERSON>, 18, of <LOCATION> Costa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mesa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif </LOCATION>. Authorities have not identified which one was the informant. Police Capt. <PERSON> Pat </PERSON> <PERSON> Rhames </PERSON> said <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON> apparently was not involved directly in the shootings. One of the downed agents fired before backup agents arrived and began shooting, <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> said. It was not known if any suspects were shot, but one was bleeding, said Sgt. <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Dyer </PERSON>, head of the SWAT team that sealed off the area. Two suspects sped off in a station wagon and two others ran in opposite directions, <PERSON> Dyer </PERSON> said. The car was abandoned a few blocks away. Police arrested the first suspect within an hour of the shooting, and the final suspect was dragged out of a yard around 7:20 a.m., police said.
