<HEAD>Truck Drives off Bridge; 40 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A truck filled with laborers and children veered off a bridge and plunged into a rain-swollen river Thursday, killing at least 40 people, officials said. More than 50 people were believed to be in the truck when it crashed through a bridge rail and fell 50 feet into the <LOCATION> Olifants </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>, 150 miles north of <LOCATION> Cape </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Town </LOCATION>, police said. The passengers were black women farmworkers and about 10 children who were being transported from a farm to their home. Ten people survived by swimming to shore or clinging to branches until they were rescued, police said.
