ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> placed <PERSON> Waldheim </PERSON> on a list of people barred from the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> after finding he participated in the execution of hostages and mistreatment of Allied prisoners. <PERSON> Howe </PERSON> wrote British Member of Parliament <PERSON> Greville </PERSON> <PERSON> Janner </PERSON> in 1986 that his own investigation had determined the four commandos were held in a Gestapo jail. But the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> study says there was no Gestapo jail in <LOCATION> Salonika </LOCATION> and the men were not interrogated by the Gestapo, the <ORGANIZATION> WJC </ORGANIZATION> said. According to the report, the British prisoners `` suffered ill treatment'' at the hands of Wermacht personnel working at the detention center, the <ORGANIZATION> WJC </ORGANIZATION> said.
