<DATELINE>CAPE TOWN, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police marched through townships firing shotguns and tear gas to break up rallies by people protesting the segregated national elections, and at least 25 people were killed, activists said today. Media reports and a church monitoring group said at least 100 people were injured in more than 20 townships, and one police officer said other officers caused the unrest by indiscriminately beating and whipping blacks. <PERSON> Essa </PERSON> <PERSON> Moosa </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Associates </ORGANIZATION>, a <LOCATION> Cape </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Town </LOCATION> law firm, said 25 people died Wednesday night and early today in seven black and mixed-race townships outside the city. More violence broke out this afternoon, with white riot squads firing shot guns and tear gas at crowds of dancing and chanting young people in the <LOCATION> Lavender </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION> township near <LOCATION> Cape </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Town </LOCATION>, a journalist on the scene said. There was no word on casualties. `` They -LRB- police -RRB- got out of the van and ran down to the road where the students were coming and started firing. There was a lot of tear gas,'' said the journalist, speaking on condition of anonymity. Anglican Archbishop <PERSON> Desmond </PERSON> <PERSON> Tutu </PERSON> said earlier today that 23 people had been killed during election day violence, adding: `` We expect the numbers of the dead to grow.'' Police Maj. <PERSON> Reg </PERSON> <PERSON> Crewe </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Pretoria </LOCATION> said at least seven people `` but certainly not as many as 23'' died in violence in the <LOCATION> Cape </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Town </LOCATION> area Wednesday night. He said the circumstances were being investigated. A later police statement said 12 deaths occurred in the <LOCATION> Cape </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Town </LOCATION> area: seven during violence associated with a feud between factions in the black township of <LOCATION> Khayelitsha </LOCATION