ION>. Officials said 14 Chinese military personnel have defected to <LOCATION> Taiwan </LOCATION> since 1949, when the Nationalists fled to this island after losing a civil war to the Communist forces on mainland <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> regards <LOCATION> Taiwan </LOCATION> as a renegade province and the two technically still are at war. More than a dozen Nationalist air force officers have sought asylum in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> since 1949. The most recent Nationalist defection was in February when Lt. Col. <PERSON> Lin </PERSON> <PERSON> Xianshun </PERSON> parachuted to safety as his F-5E jet crashed in a rice paddy in <LOCATION> Guangdong </LOCATION> province.
