<HEAD>Iraqis Ready To Swap POWs Unconditionally</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A top <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> official said Thursday his country is ready for a comprehensive, unconditional exchange of prisoners-of-war with <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>. A former Iranian official still close to the government declared there has never been a better time for reaching a full peace settlement with <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION>. Speaking at the summit of the non-aligned movement in <LOCATION> Belgrade </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> Deputy Premier <PERSON> Taha </PERSON> <PERSON> Yassin </PERSON> <PERSON> Ramadan </PERSON> said his country was prepared for a full exchange of all POWs with <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>, regardless of the lack of progress on other issues in the peace talks. His remarks were carried by the <ORGANIZATION> Iraqi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, monitored in <LOCATION> Nicosia </LOCATION>. Talks on implementing U.N. Resolution 598, which halted the war Aug. 20, 1988, began five days after the cease-fire. But the talks stalled almost immediately and have been deadlocked since. The last round of talks, held in <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION> in April, broke down in an acrimonious stalemate. The deadlocked peace talks have left an estimated 100,000 men held by both sides languishing in POW camps. The <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, monitored in <LOCATION> Nicosia </LOCATION>, quoted <PERSON> Mohammad </PERSON> <PERSON> Javad </PERSON> <PERSON> Larijani </PERSON>, a former deputy foreign minister close to newly elected President <PERSON> Hashemi </PERSON> <PERSON> Rafsanjani </PERSON>, as writing that `` There has never been such a good chance of attaining peace as there is now. One should appreciate such chances.'' <PERSON> Larijani </PERSON>, whose remarks quoted by <ORGANIZATION> IRNA </ORGANIZATION> were