sted Miichel.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BARTON REPPERT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> ambassador to <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> McCarthy </PERSON>, said Thursday he hopes to be able to return to <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> `` as soon as the situation is calm again.'' <PERSON> McCarthy </PERSON> and 29 members of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Embassy staff were evacuated from <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> Wednesday after a Christian commander in the embattled city had voiced threatening remarks. <PERSON> McCarthy </PERSON> spoke briefly with reporters when he arrived at <LOCATION> Dulles </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> on a flight from <LOCATION> Frankfurt </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. `` Any embassy has to rely on the host government authorities to provide protection,'' he said. `` When we felt that that was n't being provided any more, we had to leave.'' Asked whether the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> was washing its hands of <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>, <PERSON> McCarthy </PERSON> replied: `` Never. We're very interested in what's happening in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. We have a strong attachment to the <LOCATION> Lebanese </LOCATION> people.'' The ambassador was asked whether the evacuation of him and the embassy staff would have any impact on efforts to free Western hostages believed held in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>. <PERSON> McCarthy </PERSON> said that while the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION> was located in <LOCATION> Christian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>, the hostages are believed to be held captive in <LOCATION> Moslem </LOCATION> <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>. Movements of Americans assigned to the embassy had been restricted to <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>. For that reason, he said, `` our absence from <