<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet3pm     09-07 0302</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 3pm,0318</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market edged upward today, bidding to rebound from Wednesday's broad decline. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which fell 24.89 points on Wednesday, rose 2.28 to 2,722.07 by 3 p.m. today on Wall Street. Gainers outnumbered losers by about 7 to 6 in the overall tally of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 753 up, 645 down and 575 unchanged. Analysts said traders had been encouraged to see the market stabilize in late trading Wednesday after an early selloff. They also noted a positive response to a strong showing by the dollar in foreign exchange today. In the last few days a debate has heated up on Wall Street over whether stocks are due for a pullback after their sharp runup to record highs this summer. The optimists argue, however, that the market's rise has not yet produced the excesses of speculation and exuberance that typically occur when prices are peaking out. <ORGANIZATION> Allergan </ORGANIZATION> led the active list, down 3 | at 20 The company said its sales this year would n't grow as much as it previously projected. Airline stocks were weak for the second straight session as traders continued to cash in the issues' dramatic gains of late. AMR fell 2 -RRB- to 84 |; <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> 4 ~ to 282, and <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lines </ORGANIZATION> 3 -RRB- to 76 Applied Biosystems tumbled 4 to 24 -LCB- in the over-the-counter market. The company said its earnings for the quarter ending Sept. 30 would fall hort of their level in the comparable period a year ago. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks rose .23 to 194.41. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was up .63 at 383.50. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 130.51 million shares with an hour to go.
