<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 168,153 cars and light trucks this week, down 11.3 percent from last week's 189,705, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday. This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago, in which 191,691 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal said. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> automakers were scheduled to make 102,126 cars this week, compared with 121,653 a week ago and 121,647 in the same week in 1988. Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 66,027, compared with last week's 68,052 and last year's 70,044. Canadian automakers were to build 15,976 cars this week, down from 17,179 a week ago and down from last year's 16,251. Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 17,559, compared with 19,724 a week ago and 17,089 in the same week last year.
