. It encountered trouble in the early 1980s because of a soft computer market, a fight with stockholders who claimed in a lawsuit the company misled them, and an inability to sell <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION> real estate and lease office space in Datapoint-owned buildings.
